odernist Revolution of the Group of Seven|date=2010|publisher=Douglas & McIntyre|year=|isbn=978-1-55365-807-8|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=WGjfZPizNQIC|location=|pages=|language=en|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Klages|first1=Gregory|title=The Many Deaths of Tom Thomson: Separating Fact from Fiction|date=2016|publisher=Dundurn|location=Toronto|pages=|year=|isbn=978-1-45973-196-7|ref=harv}} * {{cite book |last1=McKay |first1=Marylin J. |title=Picturing the Land: Narrating Territories in Canadian Landscape Art, 1500-1950. |date=2011 |publisher=McGill-Queen's University Press |location=Montreal |ref=harv|isbn=978-0-77353-817-7}} * {{cite magazine |last=Mortimer-Lamb|first=Harold|author-link=Harold Mortimer-Lamb|date=March 29, 1919|title=Letter to the editor, with attached draft article|url= |magazine=Studio Magazine |location= |publisher= |doi=|pmid=|access-date=|pages=|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Murray|first1=Joan|author1-link=Joan Murray (art historian)|title=Tom Thomson: The Last Spring|date=1994|publisher=Dundurn|location=Toronto|isbn=978-1-55002-218-6|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Murray|first1=Joan|title=Tom Thomson: Design for A Canadian Hero|date=1998|publisher=Dundurn|location=Toronto|isbn=978-1-55002-315-2|author-mask=3|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Murray|first1=Joan|title=Tom Thomson: Trees|date=1999|publisher=McArthur & Co.|location=Toronto|isbn=978-1-55278-092-3|author-mask=3|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Murray|first1=Joan|editor1-last=Reid|editor1-first=Dennis|title=Tom Thomson|chapter=Tom Thomson's Letters|date=2002a|publisher=Art Gallery of Ontario/National Gallery of Canada|location=Toronto/Ottawa|pages=297–306|author-mask=3|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-55365-493-3}} * {{cite book|last1=Murray|first1=Joan|editor1-last=Reid|editor1-first=Dennis|title=Tom Thomson|chapter=Chronology|date=2002b|publisher=Art Gallery of Ontario/National Gallery of Canada|location=Toronto/Ottawa|pages=307–317|author-mask=3|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-55365-493-3}} * {{cite book|last1=Murray|first1=Joan|title=Rocks: Franklin Carmichael, Arthur Lismer, and the Group of Seven|date=2006|publisher=McArthur & Co.|location=Toronto|pages=92–7|author-mask=3|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-55278-616-1}} * {{cite web |last1=Murray|first1=Joan|title=Thomson-Algonquin / Algonquin-Thomson|url=http://tomthomsoncatalogue.org/page/?name=essay_thomson|website=tomthomsoncatalogue.org|publisher=Tom Thomson Catalogue|accessdate=22 August 2018|date=2015|author-mask=3|ref=harv}} * {{cite book |last1=Northway |first1=Mary L. |title=Nominigan: The Early Years |date=1970 |publisher=University of Toronto Press |location=Toronto|ref=harv}} * {{cite journal|last1=Reid|first1=Dennis|title=Photographs by Tom Thomson (1970)|journal=National Gallery of Canada Bulletin/Galerie nationale du Canada Bulletin|date=1971|volume=16|pages=2–36|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Reid|first1=Dennis|editor1-last=Reid|editor1-first=Dennis|title=Tom Thomson|chapter=Tom Thomson and the Arts and Crafts Movement in Toronto|date=2002|publisher=Art Gallery of Ontario/National Gallery of Canada|location=Toronto/Ottawa|pages=65–83|author-mask=3|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-55365-493-3}} * {{cite book|last1=Silcox|first1=David P.|title=The Group of Seven and Tom Thomson|date=2006|publisher=Firefly Books|location=Richmond Hill|pages=|year=|isbn=978-1-55407-154-8|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Silcox|first1=David P.|title=Tom Thomson: Life and Work|date=2015|publisher=Art Canada Institute|location=Toronto|pages=|year=|isbn=978-1-48710-075-9|url=https://www.aci-iac.ca/art-books/tom-thomson|author-mask=3|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Silcox|first1=David P.|last2=Town|first2=Harold|author2-link=Harold Town|title=The Silence and the Storm|date=|publisher=McClelland and Stewart|year=2017|edition=Revised, Expanded|isbn=978-1-44344-234-3|location=Toronto|pages=|author1-mask=3|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last1=Silcox|first1=David P.|editor1-last=Milroy|editor1-first=Sarah|editor2-last=Dejardin|editor2-first=Ian A. C. |title=David Milne: Modern Painting |chapter=A Radical Shift at Six Mile Lake |date=2018 |publisher=Philip Wilson Publishers |location=London |isbn=978-1-78130-061-9 |pages=179–81|author1-mask=3|ref=harv}} * {{cite book|last=Stacey|first=Robert|editor1-last=Reid|editor1-first=Dennis|editor2-last=Hill|editor2-first=Charles C.|title=Tom Thomson|chapter=Tom Thomson as Applied Artist|date=2002|publisher=Art Gallery of Ontario/National Gallery of Canada|location=Toronto/Ottawa|pages=47–63|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-55365-493-3}} * {{cite book|last=Wadland|first=John|editor1-last=Reid|editor1-first=Dennis|title=Tom Thomson|chapter=Tom Thomson's Places|date=2002|publisher=Art Gallery of Ontario/National Gallery of Canada|location=Toronto|pages=85–109|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-55365-493-3}} * {{cite book|last1=Webster-Cook|first1=Sandra|last2=Ruggles|first2=Anne|editor1-last=Reid|editor1-first=Dennis|title=Tom Thomson|chapter=Technical Studies on Thomson's Materials and Working Methods|date=2002|publisher=Art Gallery of Ontario/National Gallery of Canada|location=Toronto|pages=145–51|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-55365-493-3}} {{refend}}
